		<td><b>wiring a famicom board to an NROM board</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />i heard this is possible to do if you want to play a famicom game on a Nes.  i know about 60-72 pin adapters, but they are hard to come by and i have alot of NROM boards and was planning on making a few repros that would be permanent.  anybody ever do this?  is there a wiring schematic anywhere?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
