	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I believe he meant the ROM chips are compatible. They have the same number of pins and can be transferred from a japanese board to an american board without problems. The software inside the chips is always compatible too, because both regions are NTSC.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


